==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bulrush
<hw>Bul"rush`</hw> <pr>(b⟦usdot⟧l"r⟦ucr⟧sh`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[OE. <ets>bulrysche</ets>, <ets>bolroysche</ets>; of uncertain
origin, perh. fr. <ets>bole</ets> stem + <ets>rush</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A kind of large rush, growing in wet land or in
water.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The name <ex>bulrush</ex> is applied in England
especially to the cat-tail (<spn>Typha latifolia</spn> and <spn>Typha
angustifolia</spn>) and to the lake club-rush (<spn>Scirpus
lacustris</spn>); in America, to the <spn>Juncus effusus</spn>, and also
to species of <gen>Scirpus</gen> or club-rush.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bulse</ent>⟦br⟧
